<br>
This reminds me SO much of some rangers at the time of the nerf.<br>
<br>
Oh yes the monk nerf was <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>needed</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, oh yes monks were <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>overpowered</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, monks should just <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>STFU</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, monk got what they <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>deserved</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and should stop whining [based purely in class envy I'm sure] etc., etc they said (whilst sporting sigs with crits for 2000+).<br>
<br>
Then VI mentioned that bow damage was being looked at..... all of a sudden those <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>VERY SAME</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> rangers were screaming that they'd quit the game IF bow damage was nerfed. How nerfs were <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>BAD</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, how nerfs were <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>NOT</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the way to progress the game.  Hehe. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Aroth, you appear to be missing a major problem that is surrounding the whole monk &quot;Nerf&quot; issue. It all boils down to ...it wasn't really ever a problem intrinsic to the monk class.... that class was decent until a point they were designed around was removed.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Now you see that's just it.<br>
VI's sloppy itemisation (and limitations within the game itself lets not forget) created a situation where monks <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">with good enough gear</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> (which was NOT every monk, perhaps 5% of monks, probably LESS) could in some situations tank better than most anyone.<br>
<br>
So what did VI do to fix this?<br>
<br>
1. they nerfed the ass out of monk mitigation so that a monk gets much less mitigation AC from the same piece of leather armor that a warrior might wear.<br>
<br>
2. they changed the mob in PoP so that monks wouldn't have been the choice of tank anyway, without the HP or the ability to hold agro that is so important with the amount of damage they deal out.<br>
<br>
3. they reduced the AC on new monk PoP to that of druid AC.<br>
<br>
So you see monks have been effectively nerfed 3 time over for the same problem.  (admittedly they weren't all perhaps DIRECTED at monks, but they hit them never the less).<br>
<br>
<br>
There was no real issue in most of the game, besides class envy and jealousy, only at the highest of gear levels did it really become a problem.<br>
<br>
And don't forget <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>originally</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> monks had the highest innate defense, something that they lost when kunark came out and other classes caught up at 60.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>That and monks really aren't that hurting over this. Most of them are doing more then fine these days. They are just back to their old roles...pulling and damage. And realistically, damage stacks, it doesn't matter if you are 5 or 10% worse then the &quot;best damage class&quot; , you are still a very viable option.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Monks aren't hurting. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
I suggest you ask a few.<br>
<br>
Ok you've got a PoP group.<br>
Can a monk heal?  Nope.<br>
Can a monk slow? Nope.<br>
Can a monk tank well?  Nope. (both because of their defence and HP's and because they have no way to reliably keep agro - <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>WARRIORS</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> are suffering from this vs. spellcasting melees and they HAVE taunt, so how is a monk being what 5th or 6th choice a viable option?)<br>
Can a monk deal damage?  Yes.<br>
But a rogue can deal more, leaving a monk as a rogue-lite unless FD pulling.  Rangers with  agro-less bow damage outstrip monks until the highest of gear levels (don't do too bad in melee and have utitilty), mages and pets out damage (again with utility), BL's have the damage (again with lots of utility), wizzy can churn out the fast damage needed in phenomal amounts.<br>
So people would take a monk for damage dealing as what?  4th or 5th choice.<br>
<br>
Can monks pull?  Yep.  But unless it's an indoor zone where FD is pretty much vital (and even there SK's can do a passable job), lull classes can do a much more efficent and quicker job.  Not to mention that the higher damage monks now take mean a LOT more stuns, and that a lot of monk defence does NOT work when the mob is behind you. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
So how is being at best 3 or 4th best at anything a viable role?  (and don't forget <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>ALL</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> pure melees, warriors, rogues AND monks are having problems with PoP, monk are just having the most - having the general pure melee problems combined with the mitigation nerf problems)<br>
<br>
<br>
If what you're stating was true rangers would have been <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>FINE</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> post kunark.<br>
<br>
Yet was that the case?<br>
<br>
Or did rangers suffer badly for a long time before VI finally realised their mistakes and eventually correct them, in stages until their last defence upgrade in the very same patch that nerf monks?<br>
<br>
<br>
How would mages react if every single pet you had suddenly started taking between 10-15% more damage on light blue mobs to 30-50% on high con mobs?<br>
<br>
Let me guess mages would just say &quot;Ah.... well VI's right we needed this, lets just get on with the game and make the best of it that we can. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> &quot;. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bloodlilly>Bloodlilly</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#333333>(2/21/03 2:45:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8828.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: .</span><hr size=1> /mourn horse <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=382542">Moonlilly</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>
